-- French Vine Development Seen by Ciatti Slowed After Rain in June
-- B y   C l a u d i a   C a r p e n t e r
-- 2013-07-10T05:25:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-10/french-vine-development-seen-by-ciatti-slowed-after-rain-in-june.html
Wet and cold weather in June in
France, especially Bordeaux, Loire Valley and Burgundy, is not
helping vine development, which is two to three weeks behind
schedule, according to wine and grape broker Ciatti Co.  In California, producers are wondering if they will have
enough storage space for incoming fruit after a record 2012
crop,  San Rafael , California-based Ciatti, which says it’s the
world’s largest broker of bulk wines, said in a report e-mailed
yesterday.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net  